The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: India shared the honours with South Africa after the final of the Emerging Players Tournament (EPT) was washed out in Brisbane, according to a media release. The decider between India and South Africa at Brisbanes Allan Border Field was abandoned without a single ball being bowled due to persistent rain. The third-place playoff match between New Zealand and the Australian Institute of Sport (AIS) at the University ground was also called off due to heavy rains.        
	Celadna: An erratic two-over 74 pushed India golfer Shiv Kapur 13 places down the rung to tied 14th, after the second round of the Czech Open golf tournament of the European tour. SSP Chowrasia carded a dismal eight-over 80 to fall by the wayside. At the top, it is a two-way tie between Swedes Peter Hanson (70) and Fredrik Widmark (67) for a total of seven-under 37.         
	Lisbon: Indian football team went down 0-1 to Portuguese second division side Clube Desportivo de Mafra in their second practice match of the week, at the Mafra ground, on Thursday. Mafra striker Bonifacio scored the lone goal of the match in the 52nd minute to hand India their second defeat in the two-month-long training-cum-competition tour of Portugal.        
	London: Octopus oracle Paul, who grabbed fame by predicting the result of each of Germanys matches correctly at this years World Cup, has been appointed as an ambassador to Englands bid to host the 2018 World Cup.         
	London: Manchester United defender Rio Ferdinand will be out of action until the end of September after suffering knee ligament damage on the first day of training in South Africa. Confirming this news, on Friday, club manager Alex Ferguson dismissed concerns about the players back problem that plagued him last season.         
	Manchester: Manchester United says defender Nemanja Vidic has signed a new four-year contract with the club until the summer of 2014. The 28-year-old Serbia centreback is said to have signed a deal to commit his long-term future to the club.                                                                                                                                                      
